{
  "stem": "20142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, Germans incited the public that if there were Jews, to throw them out of the line.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They have to go to special stores.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when these people went to special stores, there was not sufficient amount of food left to-- to be distributed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were-- they were announcing these stores-- as long as they had the bread or whatever provision they were selling, then they came out out of stories there's not enough food for the Polish population.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jews have to go to their own local stores and to ask in Jewish community center where the stores exist.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish population mainly was living within a certain district that they could be reached and recognized as a Jewish quarters, where later around the Germans created the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there's some people there that did not look Jewish and they actually could not tell.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were cases that people could tell.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were wearing special garb like a head--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--or long caftan.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they had beards with locks on the side and wearing [INAUDIBLE] and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were fortunate enough that we had many Polish friends who were bringing for us the material to the-- like bread and other provisions-- to our house.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, there were people that were standing in line, Jewish people standing in line to-- to buy bread or other provisions, milk and whatever.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while they were standing on line, they were German who were living in Lodz and they started beating them up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had-- we knew that they were local Germans because they were wearing civilian clothing with the armband and the hakenkruis on it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were told to suddenly jam into everybody.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
